snippet.textDisplay: Guys when you look back at last week's episode when they were at the table Kenya asked "should you tell a girlfriend if her man gave out his number to another girl" and listen to Tanya's quiet response which was  "Well, That's not cheating"...so to me, that tells me that Tanya is willing to stay with Paul even when he displays suspicious behavior which is her choice and perrogative. I like Tanya but she shouldnt get mad at Kenya in this particular case because her and Kenya aren't close girlfriends. In my opinion, Cynthia or Kandi should've been the ones to tell Tanya privately. I like Kenya but we know how messy she can get sometimes and Kenya could've got a whole lot messier at that table in Toronto but she restrained herself. Btw, the only reason why Cynthia told Tanya days later about the details concerning "Cookie Lady" is because she knew it would air months later on tv and would therefore make her look disloyal for not telling Tanya earlier. The bottom line is that Tanya is the girl that would likely believe Paul no matter what ...even if the girls had receipts. She's emotionally invested in Paul and she ain't giving him up easily. She's the girl that's more likely to drop the friend versus the man if her girlfriend tells her that her man might be cheating.
